name: Urban Archaeology #006 - System Shock
description:
Genuine original still photography series.
Staircase in mansion in England, built in 1841 and destroyed by fire in 2004.
The house was a family estate and then used as an RAF hospital from WWII onward. It was said to be haunted by "the grey lady" and the spirit of a young servant girl who would appear at the foot of guests' beds, sobbing and talking of "the devilish man who did this to me".
